\section{Results}
\subsection{Single-Scenario Illustration}
Figure~\ref{fig:traj} (\texttt{results-11.png}) depicts one representative trajectory on an ErdÅ‘sâ€“RÃ©nyi layer (A) and BarabÃ¡siâ€“Albert layer (B) with \(\tau_{1}=\tau_{2}=1.5\).  Meme~A quickly rises to a peak prevalence of 39.6\%, eventually stabilising at 25.2\%, whereas meme~B dies out by \(t\approx20\).  The outcome matches the mean-field prediction because Aâ€™s eigenvector centrality concentrates on high-degree nodes absent in layer~B.

